#architecture #overview

> Four-module layered design: parser → store → CLI/server, one-way data flow.

Four-module design. Each module has a single responsibility and no upward dependencies.

  eshp_parser.py  — pure parse/render, no I/O side effects
  eshp_store.py   — SQLite graph store, no CLI or server concerns
  eshp_cli.py     — Click commands, watchdog watcher, user output
  eshp_server.py  — stdlib HTTP server for the web view (zero extra deps)

Data flows one way: .eshp file → parse_eshp() → EshpNote → store.upsert_note() → SQLite.
The CLI is the only layer allowed to call both parser and store together.
The server reads from SQLite directly (never through EshpStore) — own connection per request.
